tThere is no grief GPS -- tAmbiguity s-u-c-k-s -- tShould is a dirty word (and not the swearing kind) -- tHolidays, anniversaries, and other grief hazards -- tSecondary losses: the sneakiest bitches of them all -- tSkills and tools that help grief suck less: discovering ways to soften the hard edges of grief -- tNotice mindfully -- tImprov skills help -- tYour turn to buddy-breathe -- tSeek a creative resource -- tMake space -- tNow what? bringing curiosity to the emerging story of your life -- tThe beautiful, messy, emerging you -- tMemories for safekeeping -- tMeaning-making (even though it didn’t happen for a reason) -- tWhen grief becomes part of the story—but not the whole story -- tA little extra -- tAfterword -- tAppendix A: an alphabet of reminders for your grief journey -- tAppendix B. A letter to the grief supporters -- tAbout the author0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aA comprehensive and compassionate guide to navigating loss. When social worker Lisa Keefauver became a widow in 2011, she was alarmed to discover that even though 100 percent of us experience loss, we’re living in a grief illiterate world. In her work as a therapist, and in her search for help in the wake of her own loss, Keefauver began to see how the misguided stories we consume about grief lead to unnecessary suffering. Responding to the problematic narratives that grief is something to move on from after completing the five stages like some sort of to-do list, Keefauver became a grief activist. Through this book and her hit podcast of the same title, she creates a safe place to be inside the messiness of it all, to discover the full spectrum of grief, and to find the tools that help grievers move forward, not on. Grief is a Sneaky Bitch is a comprehensive guide—both a manual full of insights and skills and, even more importantly, a thoughtful companion that helps readers feel seen and held. Keefauver shares her personal and professional wisdom alongside the lessons she’s learned from clinicians, authors, poets, and friends. In place of rigid instructions and must-do checklists, Grief is a Sneaky Bitch invites reflection, encourages self-compassion, and explores the therapeutic power of humor with, yes, a bit of profanity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aBereavement. 0aConsolation. 0aGrief. 0aLoss (Psychology). 0aSelf-help techniques. 7aSELF-HELP / General.2bisacsh  agrieving, grief literacy, mindfulness practices, Grief is a Sneaky Bitch podcast, Reimagining Grief, social work, The 5 Ws of grief, grief guides, self-help, wellness, Grief Support, Coping With Loss, Grief Podcast, Grief Companion Guide, Emotional Healing, Grief Wisdom, Loss And Bereavement.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Texas Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311079783140uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/32299440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781477329313423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781477329313/original  a978-3-11-079783-1  University of Texas Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles